      h2 Install
      :markdown
        ```bash
        # compatible with browserify and webpack
        $ npm install biu.js --save
        
        # then include the base styles
        # <link href="/path/to/biu.css" ...
        # or import 'biu.js/dist/biu.css'
        ```
      h2 Basic Usage
      :markdown
        ```javascript
        import biu from 'biu.js'
        biu('text you want to show')
        biu('text with a type', {type: 'success'})
        biu('do not auto hide me', {autoHide: false})
        ```
      button.button(onclick="biu('It works!', {closeButton: '<i class=\"fa fa-close\"></i>'})") Default
      button.button(onclick="biu('done!', {type: 'success', closeButton: '<i class=\"fa fa-close\"></i>'})") Success
      button.button(onclick="biu('info not to be auto hidden', {type: 'info', autoHide: false})") Info
      button.button(onclick="biu('You are restricted to do this!', {type: 'warning'})") Warning
      button.button(onclick="biu('I will never go away, unless you force me to!', {type: 'danger', autoHide: false})") Danger
      button.button(onclick="biu('Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisicing elit. Earum alias rem doloremque, iusto minus culpa ipsam deleniti, praesentium, quidem ratione soluta et. Blanditiis nemo dolorem, eius officia, aut explicabo culpa. Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisicing elit. Ipsam autem repellendus nesciunt dolore, assumenda molestiae cum doloremque porro repudiandae magni quasi sequi, quos, incidunt ratione recusandae est. Deserunt, minus, perspiciatis.', {closeButton: '<i class=\"fa fa-close\"></i>', autoHide: false, align: 'left', type: 'danger'})") Large
      h2 Advanced
      :markdown
        ```javascript
        // default options
        biu('', {
          type: 'default',
          // auto-hide in specific timeout
          autoHide: true,
          timeout: 3000,
          // use font-awesome if you like!
          // closeButton: '<i class="fa fa-close"></i>',
          closeButton: 'Ã—',
          // where to append element
          el: document.body,
          // how to align text
          align: 'center',
          // whether to pop up the element in horizontal center
          pop: false,
          // trigger after element is hidden
          onHidden() {}
        })
        ```
      h2 Biu in elements other than body
      div.element#element
        span.sandbox 
          button.hey(onclick="biu('Wow, how kimochi it is...',{autoHide:false,el: document.getElementById('element'),type:'success'})") Touch me
      h2 Trigger hide
      :markdown
        ```javascript
        const tip = biu('hello', {autoHide: false})
        
        // when it's time to hide it, just call:
        tip.hide()
        ```
      h2 Pop mode
      :markdown
        ```javascript
        biu('hello', {pop: true})
        ```
      button.button(onclick="biu('Neat one!', {autoHide: false, pop: true, closeButton: '<i class=\"fa fa-close\"></i>'})") Pop me!
      h2 Call function after the element is hidden but before it gets destroyed
      :markdown
        ```javascript
        biu('how is it?', {
          onHidden() {
            alert('bye!')
          }  
        })
        ```
      button.button(onclick="biu('how is it?', {onHidden: function() {alert('bye')}})") Trigger!
      h2 Prompt user
      :markdown
        ```javascript
        const template = `Enter your name: <input id="prompt" type="text"/>
          <button id="ok" class="button">OK!</button>`
          
        const tip = biu(template, {
          autoHide: false,
          onHidden() {
            const name = document.querySelector('#prompt').value
            biu(`hello ${name}`, {pop: true})
          }  
        })
        
        document.getElementById('ok').addEventListener('click', () => {
          tip.hide()
        }, false)
        ```
